---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "DGRO Dividend History, Yield & Analysis (2026)",
  description: "Complete DGRO ETF analysis: dividend history, yield trends, top holdings, sector breakdown, and comparison vs SCHD, VIG, VYM. Updated March 2026.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-28",
};
---

<SiteLayout site="westmount" {meta}>
  <style>
    /* Base styles */
    .dgro-page {
      background: #060a12;
      color: #ffffff;
      font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    
    .container {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }
    
    .card {
      background: #0a1020;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    
    .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); }
    .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); }
    .grid-6 { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr)); }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .grid-6 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
      .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }

    /* Typography */
    h1 { 
      font-size: 2.5rem; 
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; 
      color: #ffffff;
    }
    
    h2 { 
      font-size: 1.8rem; 
      margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0; 
      color: #4a8fe7;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #152040;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    h3 { 
      font-size: 1.3rem; 
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0; 
      color: #ffffff;
    }
    
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: #a0a9b8;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    
    .mono {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }

    /* Stats grid */
    .stat-card {
      background: #0a1020;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
      border-radius: 6px;
    }
    
    .stat-value {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #48bb78;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }
    
    .stat-label {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #a0a9b8;
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }

    /* Charts */
    .chart-container {
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      position: relative;
    }
    
    .dividend-chart {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-end;
      height: 300px;
      gap: 2px;
      padding: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .dividend-bar {
      flex: 1;
      background: #4a8fe7;
      min-height: 10px;
      position: relative;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background-color 0.3s;
    }
    
    .dividend-bar:hover {
      background: #6ba3f0;
    }
    
    .bar-tooltip {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 100%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      background: #0a1020;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      white-space: nowrap;
      opacity: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
      transition: opacity 0.3s;
    }
    
    .dividend-bar:hover .bar-tooltip {
      opacity: 1;
    }
    
    .holdings-chart {
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .holding-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
    }
    
    .holding-name {
      width: 80px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-right: 1rem;
    }
    
    .holding-bar {
      flex: 1;
      height: 20px;
      background: #152040;
      border-radius: 10px;
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }
    
    .holding-fill {
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #4a8fe7, #6ba3f0);
      transition: width 0.8s ease;
    }
    
    .holding-percent {
      position: absolute;
      right: 8px;
      top: 50%;
      transform: translateY(-50%);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #ffffff;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }

    /* Sector breakdown */
    .sector-chart {
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .sector-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
    }
    
    .sector-color {
      width: 16px;
      height: 16px;
      border-radius: 3px;
      margin-right: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .sector-name {
      width: 140px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    
    .sector-bar {
      flex: 1;
      height: 16px;
      background: #152040;
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin: 0 0.5rem;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    
    .sector-fill {
      height: 100%;
      transition: width 0.8s ease;
    }
    
    .sector-percent {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      color: #a0a9b8;
      min-width: 35px;
    }

    /* Comparison table */
    .comparison-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .comparison-table th,
    .comparison-table td {
      padding: 0.8rem;
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #152040;
    }
    
    .comparison-table th {
      background: #0a1020;
      color: #4a8fe7;
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
    }
    
    .comparison-table th:hover {
      background: #152040;
    }
    
    .comparison-table tr:nth-child(even) {
      background: #0a1020;
    }
    
    .comparison-table tr:hover {
      background: #152040;
    }
    
    .sort-indicator {
      margin-left: 0.25rem;
      opacity: 0.5;
    }

    /* Calculator */
    .calculator {
      background: #0a1020;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }
    
    .input-group {
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .input-group label {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: #a0a9b8;
    }
    
    .input-group input,
    .input-group select {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      background: #060a12;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: #ffffff;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }
    
    .calc-result {
      background: #152040;
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .result-item {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
    }
    
    .result-value {
      color: #48bb78;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    /* FAQ */
    .faq-item {
      margin: 1rem 0;
      border: 1px solid #152040;
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    
    .faq-question {
      background: #0a1020;
      padding: 1rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
    }
    
    .faq-question:hover {
      background: #152040;
    }
    
    .faq-answer {
      padding: 0 1rem;
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease, padding 0.3s ease;
    }
    
    .faq-item.active .faq-answer {
      max-height: 200px;
      padding: 1rem;
    }
    
    .faq-toggle {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }
    
    .faq-item.active .faq-toggle {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }

    /* Callout */
    .callout {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #48bb78, #38a168);
      color: #ffffff;
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .callout-value {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }

    /* Related links */
    .related-links {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    .related-link {
      background: #152040;
      color: #4a8fe7;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 20px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      transition: background-color 0.3s;
    }
    
    .related-link:hover {
      background: #1a2448;
      color: #6ba3f0;
    }

    /* Buttons */
    .btn {
      background: #4a8fe7;
      color: #ffffff;
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1rem;
      transition: background-color 0.3s;
    }
    
    .btn:hover {
      background: #6ba3f0;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="dgro-page">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section>
        <h1>DGRO — iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Focus on dividend growth, not just high yield. Quality companies that consistently raise their dividends over time.</p>
        
        <div class="grid grid-6">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">2.4%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Current Yield</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">0.08%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Expense Ratio</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">$28.2B</div>
            <div class="stat-label">AUM</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">423</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Holdings</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">2014</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Inception</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-value">55.2%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">5-Year Return</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Dividend History -->
      <section>
        <h2>Dividend History</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Quarterly Dividends (2015-2026)</h3>
          <div class="chart-container">
            <div class="dividend-chart" id="dividendChart">
              <!-- Bars will be generated by JavaScript -->
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="callout">
            <div>DGRO dividend has grown</div>
            <div class="callout-value">68%</div>
            <div>over the last 5 years</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Top Holdings -->
      <section>
        <h2>Top 10 Holdings</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="holdings-chart">
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">MSFT</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="3.8"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">3.8%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">AAPL</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="3.5"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">3.5%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">JPM</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="2.8"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">2.8%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">ABBV</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="2.5"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">2.5%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">JNJ</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="2.3"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">2.3%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">BRK.B</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="2.1"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">2.1%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">HD</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="2.0"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">2.0%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">PG</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="1.9"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">1.9%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">XOM</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="1.8"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">1.8%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="holding-item">
              <div class="holding-name">MA</div>
              <div class="holding-bar">
                <div class="holding-fill" data-width="1.7"></div>
                <div class="holding-percent">1.7%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Sector Breakdown -->
      <section>
        <h2>Sector Breakdown</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="sector-chart">
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #4a8fe7;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Financials</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #4a8fe7;" data-width="20"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">20%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #48bb78;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Technology</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #48bb78;" data-width="18"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">18%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #ed8936;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Healthcare</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #ed8936;" data-width="15"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">15%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #9f7aea;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Industrials</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #9f7aea;" data-width="12"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">12%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #38b2ac;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Consumer Staples</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #38b2ac;" data-width="10"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">10%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #f56565;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Energy</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #f56565;" data-width="8"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">8%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #fbb6ce;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Consumer Discretionary</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #fbb6ce;" data-width="7"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">7%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #90cdf4;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Utilities</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #90cdf4;" data-width="4"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">4%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #faf089;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Materials</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #faf089;" data-width="3"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">3%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sector-item">
              <div class="sector-color" style="background: #a0a9b8;"></div>
              <div class="sector-name">Other</div>
              <div class="sector-bar">
                <div class="sector-fill" style="background: #a0a9b8;" data-width="3"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sector-percent">3%</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Comparison Table -->
      <section>
        <h2>DGRO vs Competitors</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <table class="comparison-table" id="comparisonTable">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th data-sort="etf">ETF <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
                <th data-sort="yield">Yield <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
                <th data-sort="expense">Expense <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
                <th data-sort="aum">AUM <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
                <th data-sort="holdings">Holdings <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
                <th data-sort="strategy">Strategy <span class="sort-indicator">↕</span></th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>DGRO</strong></td>
                <td class="mono">2.4%</td>
                <td class="mono">0.08%</td>
                <td class="mono">$28.2B</td>
                <td class="mono">423</td>
                <td>Dividend Growth</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>SCHD</strong></td>
                <td class="mono">3.1%</td>
                <td class="mono">0.06%</td>
                <td class="mono">$58.4B</td>
                <td class="mono">104</td>
                <td>Quality Dividend</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>VIG</strong></td>
                <td class="mono">1.9%</td>
                <td class="mono">0.06%</td>
                <td class="mono">$89.3B</td>
                <td class="mono">320</td>
                <td>Dividend Appreciation</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>VYM</strong></td>
                <td class="mono">2.8%</td>
                <td class="mono">0.06%</td>
                <td class="mono">$56.7B</td>
                <td class="mono">447</td>
                <td>High Dividend Yield</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>NOBL</strong></td>
                <td class="mono">1.8%</td>
                <td class="mono">0.35%</td>
                <td class="mono">$12.1B</td>
                <td class="mono">66</td>
                <td>Dividend Aristocrats</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Investment Calculator -->
      <section>
        <h2>Investment Calculator</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="calculator">
            <h3>If you invested in DGRO...</h3>
            <div class="grid grid-2">
              <div class="input-group">
                <label for="amount">Investment Amount</label>
                <input type="number" id="amount" value="10000" min="100" step="100">
              </div>
              <div class="input-group">
                <label for="years">Years Ago</label>
                <select id="years">
                  <option value="1">1 year ago</option>
                  <option value="2">2 years ago</option>
                  <option value="3" selected>3 years ago</option>
                  <option value="5">5 years ago</option>
                  <option value="7">7 years ago</option>
                  <option value="10">10 years ago</option>
                </select>
              </div>
            </div>
            <button class="btn" onclick="calculateReturns()">Calculate Returns</button>
            <div class="calc-result" id="calcResult" style="display: none;">
              <div class="result-item">
                <span>Current Value:</span>
                <span class="result-value" id="currentValue">-</span>
              </div>
              <div class="result-item">
                <span>Total Dividends:</span>
                <span class="result-value" id="totalDividends">-</span>
              </div>
              <div class="result-item">
                <span>Total Return:</span>
                <span class="result-value" id="totalReturn">-</span>
              </div>
              <div class="result-item">
                <span>Annual Return:</span>
                <span class="result-value" id="annualReturn">-</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <section>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What is DGRO ETF?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>DGRO (iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF) is an ETF that tracks companies with a strong track record of dividend growth. It focuses on dividend-paying stocks in the US that have increased their dividends consistently over time, providing investors with both income and potential for dividend growth.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>DGRO vs SCHD — which is better?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>DGRO focuses on dividend growth across a broader market cap range with 420+ holdings, while SCHD targets quality dividend stocks with only 100+ holdings. SCHD has a slightly higher current yield (3.1% vs 2.4%) but DGRO offers more diversification. Your choice depends on whether you prioritize current income (SCHD) or long-term dividend growth potential (DGRO).</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>Does DGRO pay monthly dividends?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No, DGRO pays dividends quarterly (four times per year), typically in March, June, September, and December. The dividend amount has grown consistently since the fund's inception in 2014.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What is DGRO's expense ratio?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer">
